      <section eId="sec_10_10_4">
        <num>10-10.4</num>
        <heading>Power to lease in tenant for life; effect of mortgage</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_10_10_4__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The power of a tenant for life to make leases is neither\nextinguished nor suspended when such tenant executes a mortgage.  The\npower is bound by the mortgage in the same manner as the real property\nembraced therein, and the lien of the mortgagee on such power:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_10_10_4__subsec_a__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Entitles the mortgagee to an exercise of the power so far as the\nsatisfaction of the debt requires; and\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_10_10_4__subsec_a__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Causes any subsequent interest, created by the tenant for life by\nan exercise of such power, to become subject to the mortgage as if in\nterms embraced therein.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
      </section>
